In the `three.module.js` build on NPM version v0.141.0 of ThreeJS, some of the WebGL constants appear to have compiled to incorrect values. An example that I ran into is in `WebGLTextures.getInternalFormat`: https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/0c26bb4bb8220126447c8373154ac045588441de/src/renderers/webgl/WebGLTextures.js#L160-L166 The corresponding translation of this code block in `three.module.js` fills in the gl constants:
```js
	if ( glFormat === 6407 ) {

		if ( glType === 5126 ) internalFormat = 34837;
		if ( glType === 5131 ) internalFormat = 34843;
		if ( glType === 5121 ) internalFormat = 32849;

	}
```
Most of these constants, however, are incorrect. According to [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API/Constants#additional_constants_defined_webgl_2) `gl.RG` should translate to 33319, `gl.RG32F` should translate to 33328, `gl.RG16F` should translate to 33327, and `gl.RG8` should translate to 33323. These incorrect values cause the `getInternalFormat` function to return incorrect values when using those texture formats, eventually causing WebGL to throw a `texImage2D: invalid internalformat` error.

It looks like this bug is fixed on master already, however I figured it's worth creating the issue in case anyone else runs into the same problem. Feel free to close when you release.

