### Description

AnimationMixer.update(delta) does not update bones which did not change in the animation, even if they _did_ change outside of it. This is inconsistent with the override behaviour of tracked properties exhibited normally. 

I am using Skeleton.pose() to reset all the bones to their original position.
Then I'm calling AnimationMixer.update(delta) to apply my animation.
The animation is not additive.
Doing this updates only the bones where the Interpolant's value has changed since. If you use an animation with a single holding frame, it will never set the armature to that holding frame, because it's the same frame as the previous one.
This behaviour is very unexpected, and leads to obscure bugs, like the one I initially opened this issue for. 

