1.Run fiddle. The left object's animation is a single holding frame, rotated to the left. Instead, it stays locked in the Skeleton.pose() position. The right bone has a single duplicate frame. Each time it encounters it, it doesn't update the Skeleton.pose() position, and displays that instead of the animation, which we update right after.
